summary: won't you, i asked him, salt in our hair from the spray of the sea, and the roar of the waves drowned out in my ears by the...
body:
won’t you, i asked him, salt in our hair from the spray of the sea,

and the roar of the waves drowned out in my ears by the pulse of blood around my body.

won’t you, just for a little while?

he turned to me with eyes as blue as the sky

skin like silk, freckles like stars, a mouth i was sure held all the secrets of the world.

he was so beautiful and so fragile (not that i knew it then).

won’t you, i asked, and he smiled, his fingers rough on the skin of my wrist,

tracing the veins like rivers on a map, following them to my heart, where he was already buried

so deeply buried that all the queen’s councils and all the queen’s men

could not prise him out, not with kind words nor with cruelty, not even with pain.

won’t you, i asked him, won’t you love me, just for a little while?

and he said, how about forever.

won’t you - f.
